{
  "texts": [
    "This versatile software facilitates the dynamic manipulation of various mathematical entities, including points, vectors, line segments, polygons, straight lines, conic sections and functions (Hohenwarter & Fuchs, 2004).",
    "Users can modify constructions in real time by dragging objects or inputting coordinates, equations, or numerical values.",
    "Notably, empirical evidence indicates that the use of GeoGebra yields improvements in students' comprehension across a spectrum of mathematical domains, encompassing geometry, algebra and calculus (Rincon, 2009).",
    "Moreover, GeoGebra has demonstrated effectiveness in fostering meaningful learning and understanding for both students and teachers in arithmetic, geometry, algebra and calculus (Antohe, 2009; Hohenwarter et al., 2009; Zengin, 2018 Zulnaidi et al., 2020).",
    "The software encourages creative practices in both geometric and algebraic applications."
  ]
}